An Asian man scuffled with police at Glasgow airport, causing chaos.
Witness James Edgar described the scene as people ran past, prompting an evacuation.
Uncertainty loomed over whether it was a terrorist attack.
A blazing jeep rammed into the terminal, confirmed as an attack by Prime Minister Gordon Brown.
Security levels were raised, emphasizing the government's duty to protect citizens.
The incident was linked to foiled car bomb plots in London.
Two arrests were made in connection with the attacks.
Vigilance was urged as the threat level reached its peak.
